Hello again Pranay,

I think there are problems with your regular expression. Java regex syntax is described here: http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html

regex: ^(http://.*example.com/datestamp/2009(?!oct12))
url: http://www.example.com/article/2009oct09/xyz/91012026/some-page

For one thing, that won&#39;t match because the regex has &quot;datestamp&quot; where the url has &quot;article&quot;. Putting that aside though and focusing on the date matching part, something like this might work:

^http://.*&#92;.example&#92;.com/datestamp/2009oct(?:0|1[01]).*$

That should match any date that starts with 2009oct0 or 2009oct10 or 2009oct11.

Noah



